PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
I earned my Bachelor’s degree in Software Engineering from Adama Science
and Technology University, where I developed a strong foundation in software
development, object-oriented programming, and system design. My academic
journey included hands-on experience with front-end technologies such as
HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, and UI/UX principles, along with backend
exposure to Node.js and MySQL. I completed major projects including a Social
Media Management Tool and a Human Resource Management System, which
allowed me to apply both front-end and back-end development skills. I
graduated with CGPA 2.83 and Major GPA of 3.16 and am passionate about
building responsive, user-friendly web applications while continuously
expanding my expertise in modern front-end development practices.
 
